obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (35925)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35925&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `This Act may be called the Richardson and Cruddas Limited (Acquisition and`
  line `Transfer of Undertaking) Act, 1972.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (35926)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35926&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification, appoint;`
  line
  line `(b) "Custodian" means the person who is appointed, under section 10, as the Custodian of the old`
  line company;
  line
  line `(c) "Nationalised Bank" means a corresponding new bank as defined in the Banking Companies`
  line `(Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970);`
  line
  line `(d) "new company" means the Government company, formed and registered under the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), in pursuance of the provisions of section 9;`
  line
  line `(e) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(f) "old company" means the Richardson and Cruddas Limited, a company formed and registered`
  line `under the Indian Companies Act, 1913 (7 of 1913) and having its registered office in the State of`
  line `West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "scheduled bank" has the meaning assigned to it in the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), and includes a Nationalised Bank;`
  line
  line `(i) "share" means a share in the capital of the old company;`
  line
  line `(j) "Tribunal" means the Tribunal constituted under section 13.`
  line
  line `(2) Words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), have, save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, the meanings respectively`
  line `assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 31st March, 1973, vide notification No. G.S.R. 165(E), dated 12th March, 1973, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (35927)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Undertaking of the old company to vest in the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35927&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On the appointed day,`
  line `the undertaking of the old company shall stand transferred to, and vest in, the Central Government, and`
  line `that Government shall, immediately thereafter, provide, by notification, for the transfer to, and vesting in,`
  line `of such undertaking in the new company.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (35928)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `General effect of meeting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35928&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The undertaking of the old company shall be deemed to include`
  line `all assets, rights, powers, authorities and privileges and all property, movable and immovable, cash`
  line `balances, reserve funds, investments and all other rights and interests in, or arising out of, such property`
  line `as were immediately before the appointed day in the ownership, possession, power or control of the old`
  line `company in relation to the undertaking, whether within or without India, and all books of account,`
  line `registers (other than register of members and documents relating thereto), records and all other documents`
  line `of whatever nature relating thereto and shall also be deemed to include all borrowings, liabilities and`
  line `obligations of whatever kind then subsisting of the old company in relation to the undertaking.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise expressly provided by this Act, all contracts, deeds, bonds, agreements, powers`
  line `of attorney, grants of legal representation and other instruments of whatever nature subsisting or having`
  line `effect immediately before the appointed day which relate to the undertaking of the old company, shall be`
  line `of as full force and effect in favour of the Central Government, and on the transfer of such undertaking to`
  line `the new company, of such new company and may be enforced or acted upon as fully and effectively as if`
  line `they had related to the Central Government or the new company, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) If, on the appointed day, a proceeding instituted by the old company in relation to the`
  line `undertaking referred to in section 3 is pending, such proceeding may, as from that day, be continued by`
  line `the Central Government or, on the transfer of the undertaking to the new company, by the new company.`
  line
  line `(b) If, on the appointed day, any cause of action is existing against the old company in relation to the`
  line `undertaking referred to in section 3, such cause of action may, as from that day, be enforced against the`
  line `Central Government or, on the transfer of the undertaking to the new company, against the new company.`
  line
  line `(c) Save as otherwise provided in clauses (a) and (b), no suit, proceeding or cause of action by or`
  line `against the old company shall be continued or enforced by or against the Central Government or the new`
  line company
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (35929)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Duty to deliver possession of property acquired and documents relating thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35929&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where`
  line `any property has vested in the Central Government under section 3, every person in whose possession or`
  line `custody or under whose control the property may be, shall deliver the property to the Central Government`
  line forthwith.
  line
  line `(2) Any person who, on the appointed day, has in his possession or under his control any books,`
  line `documents or other papers relating to the undertaking which has vested in the Central Government under`
  line `this Act and which belong to the old company, or, would have so belonged if the undertaking of the old`
  line `company had not vested in the Central Government, shall be liable to account for the said books,`
  line `documents or other papers to the Central Government and, on the transfer of such undertaking to the new`
  line `company, to that company, and shall deliver them up to the Central Government or the new company, as`
  line `the case may be, or to such other person as the Central Government or the new company may specify in`
  line `this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may take, or cause to be taken, all necessary steps for securing`
  line `possession of all properties which have vested in that Government under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (35930)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Duty to furnish particulars.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35930&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The old company shall, within such period as the Central`
  line `Government may allow in this behalf, furnish to that Government, and the new company, a complete`
  line `inventory of all the properties and assets (including particulars of investments) of the old company on the`
  line `appointed day, all liabilities and obligations of the old company subsisting on that day and also all`
  line `agreements entered into by the old company and in force on that day including agreements, whether`
  line `express or implied, relating to leave, pension, gratuity and other terms of service of any officer or other`
  line `employee of the old company under which, by virtue of this Act, the Central Government has, or will`
  line `have, or may have, the liabilities and, for this purpose, the Central Government and the new company`
  line `shall afford the old company all reasonable facilities.`
  line
  line `(2) The old company shall, if required by the Central Government or new company so to do, furnish`
  line `such returns or information relating to the undertaking referred to in section 3, or, any person employed`
  line `by the old company for the purpose of such undertaking, as may be specified in such requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (35931)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Transfer of employees of the old company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35931&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer or other employee of the old`
  line `company (except a director or any managerial personnel specified in section 197A of the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or any other person entitled to manage the whole or a substantial part of the`
  line `business of the old company under a special agreement with that company) in the employment of the old`
  line `company immediately before the appointed day shall, in so far as such officer or other employee is`
  line `employed in connection with the affairs of the undertaking of the old company, become, as from the`
  line `appointed day, an officer or other employee, as the case may be, of the Central Government and, on the`
  line `transfer of such undertaking to the new company, of that company, and shall hold his office on the same`
  line `terms and conditions and with the same rights to pension, gratuity and other matters as would have been`
  line `admissible to him if the undertaking of the old company had not been transferred to and vested in the`
  line `Central Government or the new company, and continue to do so unless and until his employment in the`
  line `Central Government or the new company is duly terminated for until the remuneration, terms or`
  line `conditions of service are duly altered by the Central Government or the new company, as the case may`
  line `be:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the alteration so made is not acceptable to any officer or other employee, his`
  line `employment shall be terminated on payment to him by the Central Government or the new company, as`
  line `the case may be, of an amount equivalent to three months remuneration in the case of permanent`
  line `employees and one months remuneration in the case of other employees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any officer or other`
  line `employee who has, by notice in writing given to the Central Government or the new company, within`
  line `thirty days next following the appointed day, intimated his intention of not becoming an officer or other`
  line `employee of the Central Government or the new company, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) For the persons, who, immediately before the appointed day, were the trustees for any pension,`
  line `provident fund, gratuity or other like fund constituted for the officers or other employees of the old`
  line `company, there shall be substituted as trustees such persons as the Central Government or the new`
  line `company may, by general or special order, specify.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other employee from the`
  line `old company to the Central Government or the new company shall not entitle such officer or other`
  line `employee to any compensation under that Act or other law, and no such claim shall be entertained by any`
  line `court, tribunal or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (35932)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35932&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the transfer, under section 3, of the undertaking of the old company`
  line `to the Central Government, there shall be paid by the Central Government to the Custodian an amount of`
  line `rupees thirty lakhs.`
  line
  line `(2) The Custodian shall open an account in the name of the old company in any scheduled bank and`
  line `credit the said amount to the said account and hold the said amount in trust for and on behalf of the old`
  line company.
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (35933)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Formation and registration of a new company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35933&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `For the efficient management and`
  line `administration of the undertaking which will vest in the Central Government under section 3, there shall`
  line `be formed and registered, before the appointed day, a Government company, with the name "Richardson`
  line `and Cruddas (1972) Limited", in accordance with the provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (35934)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Management of the old company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35934&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The affairs of the old company shall be managed by a`
  line `Custodian to be appointed by the Central Government in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, if the Custodian declines to become, or to continue to`
  line `function as, the Custodian or if it is of opinion that it is necessary in the interests of the old company so to`
  line `do, appoint any other person as the Custodian of the old company.`
  line
  line `(2) The Custodian appointed under sub-section (1) shall receive, from the funds of the old company,`
  line `such emoluments as the Central Government may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The Custodian shall hold office during the pleasure of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (35935)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Custodian to be public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35935&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Custodian shall be a public servant within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (35936)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Vacation of office by directors, etc., of the old company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35936&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the appointment of a`
  line `Custodian, every person holding office, immediately before such appointment, as director or manager of`
  line `the old company shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or`
  line `in any decree or order of any court or tribunal, vacate such office.`
  line
  line `(2) The Custodian shall receive the sum referred to in section 8 and shall deal with the said sum for`
  line `meeting any liability which is incurred by the old company after the appointed day, and the balance, if`
  line `any, left after meeting the said liability, in accordance with the wishes of the members of the old`
  line `company, expressed in a general meeting convened by the Custodian, and the provisions of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall, so far as may be, apply to such meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The Custodian may, if the members of the old company so desire, distribute the balance referred`
  line `to in sub-section (2) amongst such members in accordance with their rights and interests and thereafter`
  line `apply to the Court for the winding up of the old company by the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (35937)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Constitution of a Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35937&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of rectification of the register of members of`
  line `the old company, the Central Government shall, by notification, constitute a Tribunal consisting of one`
  line `person who is or has been a Judge of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) If, for any reason, a vacancy (other than a temporary absence) occurs in the office of the presiding`
  line `officer of the Tribunal, the Central Government shall appoint another person, in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section, to fill the vacancy and the proceedings may be continued before the Tribunal`
  line `from the stage at which the vacancy is filled.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall make available to the Tribunal such staff as may be necessary for`
  line `the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) All expenses incurred in connection with the Tribunal shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of India.`
  line
  line `(5) The Tribunal shall have power to regulate its own procedure in all matters arising out of the`
  line `discharge of its functions including the place or places at which it shall hold its sittings:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal shall, as far as practicable, follow the procedure laid down in the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for the investigation of claims and the decision of the Tribunal shall be`
  line final.
  line
  line `(6) The Tribunal shall, for the purpose of making an inquiry under this Act, have the same powers as`
  line `are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in`
  line `respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the summoning and enforcing the attendance of any witness and examining him on oath,`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of any document or other material producible as evidence,`
  line
  line `(c) the reception of evidence on affidavits,`
  line
  line `(d) the requisitioning of any public record from any Court or office,`
  line
  line `(e) issue of any commission for the examination of witnesses.`
  line
  line `(7) Any proceeding before the Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of section 193 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and the Tribunal shall be deemed to`
  line `be a civil court for the purpose of section 195 and Chapter XXXV of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (35938)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Tribunal to call upon persons to make claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35938&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal shall, by notification and in`
  line `such other manner as may be prescribed, call upon every person, who claims to have any interest in any`
  line `share, to prefer his claim within thirty days from such date as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person claiming an interest in any share shall make his claim before the Tribunal in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed, stating therein the rights claimed by him in the share and the manner in which,`
  line `and the date on which, such right was acquired by him.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal may, if it is satisfied that any claimant had sufficient cause for not preferring the`
  line `claim within thirty days from the date specified in the notification, admit such claim within a further`
  line `period of thirty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (35939)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Determination of genuine shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35939&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal shall, after taking such evidence as may be`
  line `adduced before it and after making such inquiry as it may think fit and after hearing such persons as may`
  line `desire to be heard, determine which of the documents purporting to be shares represent, in reality, a`
  line `contribution to the capital of the old company, and on such determination, all other documents purporting`
  line `to be shares shall stand declared to be spurious and shall stand cancelled.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (35940)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `No compensation for cancellation of spurious shares.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35940&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) No holder of a document purporting`
  line `to be a share shall be entitled to claim either from the Central Government or from the old or new`
  line `company any damages for the cancellation of such document by virtue of the provisions of section 15.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), every person who had acquired a document,`
  line `purporting to be a share, bona fide for value without notice of the fact that it did not represent any`
  line `contribution to the capital of the old company, shall be entitled to claim reimbursement from the person`
  line `from whom such document was acquired by him, and, the period of limitation for any action for such`
  line `reimbursement shall be deemed to commence on the date on which the document held by him as a share`
  line `stands cancelled under section 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (35941)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of Tribunal to entertain and dispose of claims for reimbursement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35941&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `.(1) The Tribunal`
  line `shall have jurisdiction to entertain and dispose of any claim for reimbursement referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 16.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such claim shall be made before the Tribunal within thirty days from the date on which the`
  line `document purporting to be a share stands cancelled under section 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (35942)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Suits and legal proceedings, not to be commenced or proceeded with.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35942&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the`
  line `date on which the Tribunal is constituted, no suit or other legal proceeding shall be commenced, or if`
  line `pending at the date of such constitution, shall be proceeded with, against the old company except with the`
  line `leave of the Tribunal and subject to such terms as the Tribunal may impose.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the Tribunal shall have, and no court or other tribunal shall`
  line `have, jurisdiction to entertain or dispose of--`
  line
  line `(a) any suit or proceeding by, or on behalf of, or against, the old company;`
  line
  line `(b) any claim made by, or on behalf of, or against, the old company;`
  line
  line `(c) any question of priorities and any other question whatsoever, whether of law or of fact, which`
  line `may relate to, or arise in relation to, the genuineness or otherwise of, any share or in relation to any`
  line `rights or obligations under such share,`
  line `whether such suit or proceeding has been instituted, or is instituted, or such claim or question has arisen`
  line `or arises before or after the constitution of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) If, on the appointed day, any suit, appeal or other proceeding of whatever nature by or against the`
  line `old company in relation to any business of that company is pending in any court, such suit, appeal or`
  line `other proceeding shall, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or`
  line `in any contract, stand transferred to, and shall be disposed of by, the Tribunal and thereupon no other`
  line `court or tribunal shall have jurisdiction to try such suit, appeal or proceeding.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A suit or other proceeding relating to the title to, or claim in or in relation to, any share`
  line `or any document purporting to be a share shall be deemed to be a suit or other proceeding relating to the`
  line `business of the old company.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) shall apply to any petition or appeal arising out of`
  line `any petition made under article 32, article 226 or article 227 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (35943)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Decision of the Tribunal to be final.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35943&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Every decision, under this Act, of the Tribunal shall be`
  line `final and shall not be called in question in any court except by way of a petition under article 32 or`
  line `article 226 of the Constitution.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (35944)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Custodian to reconstruct register of members of the old company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35944&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Custodian shall`
  line `reconstruct the register of members of the old company and shall include therein the names of the holders`
  line `of the shares which have been declared by the Tribunal as representing, in reality, a contribution to the`
  line `capital of the old company and strike off from the register of members of the old company the names of`
  line `the holders of the documents purporting to be shares which stand, by reason of the determination made by`
  line `the Tribunal under section 15, cancelled.`
  line
  line `(2) On and from the date of reconstruction of the register of members of the old Company,--`
  line
  line `(a) the register, as so reconstructed, shall be deemed to be the register of members of the old`
  line `company, and`
  line
  line `(b) all registers of members maintained by the old company, immediately before the said date,`
  line `shall stand cancelled.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (35945)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Custodian to issue fresh share certificates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35945&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Custodian shall issue, in such form as may`
  line `be prescribed, fresh share certificate in relation to the shares which have been declared by the Tribunal as`
  line `representing, in reality, a contribution to the capital of the old company.`
  line
  line `(2) All share certificates issued by the old company before the date of the determination made by the`
  line `Tribunal shall, on and from such determination, stand cancelled.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (35956)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `No annual general meeting of the old company to be held before the reconstruction of the register of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35956&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothwithstanding anything contained in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or any other law for the time being in force, no annual or other general meeting of`
  line `the old company shall be held until the reconstruction of the register of members of the old company has`
  line `been completed in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No resolution purported to have been passed at any meeting of the members of the old company`
  line `shall, until the reconstruction of its register of members, have effect.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (35947)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Custodian to file accounts until reconstruction of the register of members of the old company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35947&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Until the register of members of the old company is finally reconstructed, the Custodian`
  line `shall file every year with the Registrar, the annual accounts of the old company.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall, as far as may be, apply to the`
  line `annual accounts referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (35948)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35948&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) having in his possession, custody or control any property forming part of the undertaking`
  line `which has vested in the Central Government under section 3, wrongfully withholds such property`
  line `from the Central Government or new company, or`
  line
  line `(b) wrongfully obtains possession of any property forming part of such undertaking, or`
  line
  line `(c) being required by sub-section (2) of section 5 so to do, wilfully withholds or fails to furnish to`
  line `the Central Government, new company or any other person specified by that Government or the new`
  line `company, any document which may be in his possession, custody or control, or`
  line
  line `(d) wilfully fails to furnish an inventory as required by section 6, or furnishes an inventory`
  line `containing any particulars which are incorrect or false in material particulars and which he either`
  line `knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true, or`
  line
  line `(e) being required by the Central Government or the new company in writing so to do, fails to`
  line `furnish any return, statement or other information relating to the undertaking of the old company`
  line `which has vested in the Central Government under section 3, or`
  line
  line `(f) makes a false or frivolous claim before the Tribunal with regard to the ownership of, or any`
  line `right in, any share, or`
  line
  line `(g) fails to comply with any order of direction made under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court trying any offence under clause (a), clause (b) or clause (c) of this sub-section`
  line `may, at the time of convicting the accused person, order him to deliver up or refund, within a period to be`
  line `fixed by the court, any property or money wrongfully withheld or wrongfully obtained or any document`
  line `wilfully withheld or not furnished.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this section except with the`
  line `previous sanction of the Central Government or an officer authorised by that Government in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (35949)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35949&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to punishment`
  line `if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised all due`
  line `diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence was committed with the consent or connivance`
  line `of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the`
  line `company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of that offence`
  line `and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (35950)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Offences to be triable by a Magistrate of the first class and not to be compoundable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35950&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898),--`
  line
  line `(a) every offence against this Act shall be triable by a Magistrate of the first class, and`
  line
  line `(b) no offence against this Act shall be compoundable.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (35951)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35951&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Custodian in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or the Custodian or the`
  line `new company for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done under this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (35952)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Contracts, etc., in bad faith may be cancelled or varied.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35952&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is`
  line `satisfied, after such inquiry as it thinks fit, that any contract or agreement entered into at any time within`
  line `twelve months immediately preceding the appointed day, between the old company and any other person`
  line `has been entered into in bad faith and is detrimental to the interests of the old company or of the new`
  line `company, it may make an order cancelling or varying (either unconditionally or subject to such conditions`
  line `as it may think fit to impose) the contract or agreement and thereafter the contract or agreement shall have`
  line `effect accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no contract or agreement shall be cancelled or varied except after giving to the parties`
  line `to the contract or agreement a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (1) may make an application to the`
  line `Tribunal for the variation or reversal of such order and thereupon the Tribunal may confirm, modify or`
  line `reverse such order`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (35953)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to terminate contract of employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35953&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `If the Custodian is of opinion that any contract`
  line `of employment entered into by or on behalf of the old company at any time before the appointed day is`
  line `unduly onerous, he may, by giving to the employee one months notice in writing or the salary or wages`
  line `for one month in lieu thereof, terminate such contract of employment.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (35954)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to remove difficulty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35954&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (35955)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191&sectionId=35955&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_14_15_00008_197278_1517807325191
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules to carry`
  line `out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form and manner in which every claim shall be preferred before the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) the form in which fresh shares shall be issued by the Custodian;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session`
  line `or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `रिचर्डसन एंड क्रूडास लिमिटेड (उपक्रम का अर्जन और अंतरण), अधिनियम 1972`
  sourceUrl `https://www.indiacode.nic.in/bitstream/123456789/1738/2/hH1972-78.pdf`
